==German==

===Alternative forms===
* {{l|de|hie}} {{qualifier|archaic; except in {{m|de|hie und da}}}}

===Etymology===
From {{inh|de|gmh|hier}}, from {{inh|de|goh|hier}}, from {{inh|de|gem-pro|*hē₂r}}. Cognate with {{cog|nl|hier}}, {{cog|en|here}}, {{cog|sv|här}}. The predominant form in Middle High German and throughout modern dialects of [[High German]] is {{m|gmh|hie}} (and variants) with loss of the final ''-r''. The form {{m|de||hier}} begins to gain ground from the late 16th century (in spite of Luther’s usage), which may point to influence by cognate {{der|de|gml|hīr}}, {{m|gml|hēr}} (where no ''r-''less form seems to exist; but compare modern {{cog|li|heej}}).

===Pronunciation===
* {{IPA|de|/hiːɐ̯/}}
* {{audio|de|De-at-hier.ogg|audio (Austria)}}
* {{audio|de|De-hier.ogg|Audio}}
* {{rhymes|de|iːɐ̯}}

===Adverb===
{{de-adv}}

# {{lb|de|location}} [[here]]; in this place; {{non-gloss definition|refers to an environment one is currently in, or to something within reach}}
#: {{ux|de|Ich bin '''hier''' in diesem Dorf geboren.|t=I was born '''here''' in this village.|inline=1}}
#: {{ux|de|Setzen wir uns '''hier''' aufs Sofa.|t=Let’s sit down '''here''' on the sofa.|inline=1}}
# {{lb|de|location}} [[there]]; right there; in that place; {{non-gloss definition|refers to something that is considered nearby, or can be seen and pointed at}}
#: {{ux|de|Die Kirche ist gleich '''hier''' am Ende der Straße.|t=The church is right '''there''' at the end of the street.|inline=1}}
#: {{ux|de|Siehst du die Wolke '''hier''' neben der Bergspitze?|t=Can you see that cloud '''there''' next to the mountain top?|inline=1}}
# {{lb|de|abstract}} [[here]] {{gloss|within this context}}
#: {{ux|de|Die Frist wurde '''hier''' überhaupt nicht erwähnt.|t=The deadline was not mentioned '''here''' at all.|inline=1}}
# {{non-gloss definition|used with the definite article or the determiner {{l|de|dieser||this, that}} to express proximity (“this”)}}
